      • removeFixedVariables

        public final int removeFixedVariables()
        Removes edges to all variables that have fixed values and modifies the factor function to incorporate those values.

        For DiscreteFactors, this will replace the factor function with one using a newly generated factor table. For other factor types this wraps the factor function with FactorFunctionWithConstants.

        Returns:
        the number of variable edges that were removed.
        See Also:
        Variable.hasFixedValue()

      • removeFixedVariablesImpl

        protected FactorFunction removeFixedVariablesImpl(FactorFunction oldFunction,
                                      @Nullable
                                      IFactorTable oldFactorTable,
                                      java.util.ArrayList<Variable> constantVariables,
                                      int[] constantIndices)
        Replaces factor function conditioned on a set of variables with fixed values that have already been removed from the factor. This should only be called from within removeFixedVariables().

        This is invoked after the fixed value variables have already been disconnected from the factor, but before the factor function has been replaced.

        Parameters:
        constantVariables - lists the variables
        constantIndices -
